UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS SB 69/EN
1 AN ACT relating to the autism spectrum disorder trust fund and declaring an
2 emergency.
3 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
4 SECTION 1. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 194A IS CREATED TO
5 READ AS FOLLOWS:
6 (1) The autism spectrum disorder trust fund is hereby created in the State Treasury
7 as a separate trust fund. The fund shall be administered by the Cabinet for
8 Health and Family Services.
9 (2) The fund shall receive amounts from grants, contributions, appropriations, or
10 other moneys made available for the purposes of the fund.
11 (3) Notwithstanding KRS 45.229, fund amounts not expended at the close of a fiscal
12 year shall not lapse but shall be carried forward to the next fiscal year.
13 (4) Moneys in the fund shall be used to support autism spectrum disorder research
14 and services for Kentuckians. Funds shall be administered and distributed by the
15 Advisory Council on Autism Spectrum Disorders created in Section 2 of this Act
16 for the purposes set forth in this section and Section 2 of this Act.
17 Section 2. KRS 194A.624 is amended to read as follows:
18 (1) The Advisory Council on Autism Spectrum Disorders is hereby created and shall be
19 attached to the Office of Autism within the Cabinet for Health and Family Services
20 for administrative purposes.
21 (2) The Advisory Council on Autism Spectrum Disorders shall consist of the following
22 members appointed by the Governor:
23 (a) One (1) representative from the Department for Public Health;
24 (b) One (1) representative from the Department for Medicaid Services;
25 (c) One (1) representative from the Department for Community Based Services;
26 (d) One (1) representative from the Department of Public Advocacy;
27 (e) One (1) representative from the Department of Education;
