1 (f) One (1) representative from the Department of Juvenile Justice;
2 (g) One (1) representative from the Department for Behavioral Health,
3 Developmental and Intellectual Disabilities;
4 (h) One (1) representative from the Office for Children with Special Health Care
5 Needs;
6 (i) One (1) parent or youth representative from the Commonwealth Council on
7 Developmental Disabilities;
8 (j) One (1) representative from the Kentucky Autism Training Center;
9 (k) One (1) representative from the Office of Vocational Rehabilitation;
10 (l) One (1) representative from the University of Louisville;
11 (m) One (1) representative from the University of Kentucky Human Development
12 Institute;
13 (n) One (1) representative from the University of Kentucky;
14 (o) One (1) representative from the Center for Autism Spectrum Evaluation,
15 Service, and Research;
16 (p) One (1) representative from the Education Professional Standards Board;
17 (q) One (1) pediatrician representative;
18 (r) One (1) representative from the Weisskopf Child Evaluation Center;
19 (s) One (1) representative from the First Steps Program;
20 (t) One (1) representative from the Arc of Kentucky;
21 (u) The director of the Office of Autism;
22 (v) At least one (1) consumer representative, an adult with a diagnosis on the
23 autism spectrum; and
24 (w) Five (5) citizen-at-large members.
25 (3) The co-chairs of the Advisory Council on Autism Spectrum Disorders shall be the
26 representatives appointed by the Governor from the University of Kentucky and the
27 University of Louisville.
